I agree, tasty but a tiny bit bland. a bit more salt perhaps. I am going to revert back to my usual using just fennel, creme fraiche, ready to use puff pastry and pecorino romano, which is saltier than parmigiana. Link here - http://www.neurotickitchen.com/2013/03/ingredient-spotlight-fennel-savory.html The result is mellow, flavorful and rich but not too heavy. Crust is not soggy either because it bakes quite hot and for 40 min,

Rating: 3
I found this very good the first time I made it, but I added red wine to the vegetable mix. The second time I made it I added a lot of garlic, the red wine and it was even better. I plan on making this again, it made a great lunch for work and is good cold.

